Allow me. At the poker table, a player who has (or wishes to represent that one has) a competitive hand and wants to stay in the game, will match or SEE the previous level of betting by betting a matching amount. 

The other choices are FOLD--a player suspects that their cards are weaker than those of others and is unwilling to bluff, so abandons any money they've already bet, and walks away; 
or RAISE--a player has strong cards (or represents so), and not only matches the prior bet but raises the amount at stake. 
Hope that's clear.

